  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance Programme (HAP) in AFghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the proposed project is to continue supporting IOM Afghanistan&apos;s Humanitarian Assistance Program (HAP), implementing modifications to enhance its impact and consolidate the gains of the last nine years. The project will provide emergency relief assistance through provision of non-food items (NFIs), emergency shelter and cash assistance for vulnerable natural disaster or conflict affected/displaced populations. The project will also provide enhanced community level preparedness and capacities by conducting community-based disaster risk management activities in selected disaster-prone communities.  Lastly the project will provide strengthening the institutional capacity of the Afghanistan National Disaster Management Authority (ANDMA) and providing technical support to provincial ANDMA offices and strengthening of the Emergency Shelter (ES)/NFI Cluster through dedicated staffing at the national and regional levels.</narrative>
  </description>
